(42, 13, 11, 19, 146, 8, 8, NULL, 'Healing the Bowed Down', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of lifting up those who are bowed down. Luke describes a woman who was unable to lift herself due to her infirmity, while Psalms speaks of the Lord raising those who are bowed down.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 11, 40, 9, 32, 33, NULL, 'Healing of Infirmity and Possession', 'Both passages emphasize miraculous healings performed by Jesus, showcasing His authority over physical ailments and spiritual oppression. The woman''s spirit of infirmity and the dumb man''s possession illustrate the diverse forms of suffering addressed by Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 12, 19, 107, 20, 20, 'thou art loosed from thine infirmity', 'Healing and Deliverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize healing and deliverance from infirmity. In Luke, Jesus directly heals a woman, while Psalms speaks of God sending His word to heal and deliver. This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention in restoring health.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 12, 40, 8, 16, 16, 'thou art loosed from thine infirmity', 'Healing and Deliverance Themes', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' authority to heal and deliver individuals from afflictions. In Luke 13:12, Jesus directly addresses a woman and declares her loosed from her infirmity, while in Matthew 8:16, He casts out spirits and heals the sick, showcasing His power over physical and spiritual ailments.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 12, 29, 3, 10, 10, 'thou art loosed from thine infirmity', 'Strength in Weakness', 'This connection highlights the theme of empowerment in both passages. In Luke, the woman is loosed from her infirmity, while in Joel, the weak declare strength, suggesting a transformation from weakness to strength.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 12, 42, 6, 8, 10, 'loosed from thine infirmity', 'Healing on the Sabbath', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' authority to heal on the Sabbath. In each instance, he restores physical health, demonstrating compassion and challenging the prevailing interpretations of the law.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 12, 42, 13, 16, 16, 'loosed from thine infirmity', 'Healing and Liberation on the Sabbath', 'Both passages emphasize the woman''s liberation from her infirmity, highlighting her status as a daughter of Abraham. This connection underscores the importance of healing and freedom from bondage, particularly on the Sabbath.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 12, 23, 65, 1, 1, NULL, 'Healing and Divine Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention and healing. In both passages, there is an emphasis on God reaching out to those who are not actively seeking Him, as seen in Jesus'' act of healing the woman and God''s declaration of being found by those who did not ask.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 13, 19, 107, 20, 22, 'glorified God', 'Healing and Praise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize healing and glorifying God. In Luke, the woman''s immediate healing leads to her glorifying God, while Psalms speaks of healing and the call to praise the Lord for His goodness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 13, 41, 16, 18, 18, NULL, 'Healing Through Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands on the sick, resulting in healing. This connection highlights the power of physical touch in the context of divine healing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 13, 41, 5, 23, 23, NULL, 'Healing through Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands for healing. In Luke, the laying on of hands results in immediate healing, while in Mark, the request is made for Jesus to lay hands on a dying daughter to bring her back to life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 13, 19, 103, 1, 5, 'glorified God', 'Healing and Praise Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing and glorifying God. In Luke 13:13, the woman''s immediate healing leads her to glorify God, paralleling Psalms 103:1-5, which calls for blessing the Lord for His benefits, including healing.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 13, 42, 17, 14, 17, 'glorified God', 'Healing and Glorifying God', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God following healing. In Luke 13:13, the woman glorifies God after being made straight, while in Luke 17:15, one healed leper returns to glorify God after his cleansing.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 13, 42, 4, 40, 40, 'he laid his hands on', 'Healing Through Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands for healing. In Luke 13:13, Jesus lays hands on a woman, resulting in her immediate healing, while in Luke 4:40, he lays hands on many sick individuals, healing them as well.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 13, 44, 9, 17, 17, 'laid his hands on her', 'Healing and Restoration Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing through the laying on of hands. Both passages emphasize the immediate restoration of sight and health, leading to glorification of God.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 14, 2, 20, 9, 9, 'six days in which men ought to work', 'Sabbath Work and Healing', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on work during the six days as stated in both passages. Luke 13:14 reflects the ruler''s insistence on adhering to the command in Exodus 20:9 about working six days, suggesting a tension between healing and sabbath observance.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 14, 40, 12, 2, 2, 'not on the sabbath day', 'Sabbath Healing Controversy', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict over healing on the Sabbath. The ruler of the synagogue in Luke expresses indignation about healing on this day, while the Pharisees in Matthew accuse Jesus'' disciples of unlawful actions on the Sabbath.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 14, 43, 9, 14, 16, 'healed on the sabbath day', 'Sabbath Healing Controversy', 'Both passages emphasize healing on the Sabbath, which incites indignation from religious leaders. The ruler in Luke expresses disapproval of healing on this day, while the Pharisees in John question Jesus'' actions, leading to division among them.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 14, 42, 6, 7, 7, NULL, 'Sabbath Healing Controversy', 'Both passages emphasize the scrutiny Jesus faced regarding healing on the Sabbath. The ruler''s indignation in Luke 13:14 reflects the same concern present in Luke 6:7, where the Pharisees watched for an accusation against him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 14, 43, 5, 15, 16, 'healed on the sabbath day', 'Sabbath Healing Controversy', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict surrounding healing on the Sabbath. In Luke, the ruler expresses indignation about healing on this day, while in John, the Jews persecute Jesus for the same reason.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 14, 41, 5, 22, 22, 'ruler of the synagogue', 'Healing on the Sabbath', 'Both passages emphasize the role of synagogue rulers in relation to Jesus'' healing activities. In Luke, the ruler expresses indignation about healing on the Sabbath, while in Mark, Jairus, a ruler of the synagogue, seeks Jesus'' help for his daughter, highlighting differing responses to Jesus'' actions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 14, 42, 8, 41, 41, 'ruler of the synagogue', 'Healing and Sabbath Observance', 'This connection highlights the role of Jairus, a ruler of the synagogue, who seeks healing for his daughter. The earlier passage shows the indignation of a synagogue ruler regarding healing on the Sabbath, emphasizing the tension between religious law and the act of healing.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 15, 42, 14, 5, 5, 'on the sabbath', 'Sabbath Care for Animals', 'Both passages emphasize the care for animals on the Sabbath, illustrating a common practice of prioritizing their needs. They highlight the idea that helping an animal in distress is permissible, even on a day of rest.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 15, 43, 7, 21, 24, 'loose his ox or his ass', 'Sabbath Healing and Work', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of performing necessary work on the Sabbath. In Luke, Jesus points out the hypocrisy of prioritizing animals'' needs over human well-being, while in John, He argues for the righteousness of healing on the Sabbath. This connection highlights the theme of mercy and necessity in relation to Sabbath observance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 15, 44, 13, 9, 10, NULL, 'Hypocrisy and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hypocrisy in religious practice. In Luke, Jesus critiques those who prioritize their own needs over righteousness, while in Acts, Paul confronts a deceiver who perverts the right ways of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 15, 18, 34, 30, 30, 'hypocrite', 'Hypocrisy and Its Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of hypocrisy in both passages. Luke 13:15 addresses the hypocrisy of prioritizing animals'' needs over human well-being, while Job 34:30 warns against the reign of hypocrites that ensnare the people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 15, 20, 11, 9, 9, 'hypocrite', 'Hypocrisy and Just Actions', 'This connection highlights the theme of hypocrisy in both passages. Luke 13:15 addresses the hypocrisy of prioritizing animals'' needs over human welfare, while Proverbs 11:9 warns that a hypocrite can harm others with their words.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 15, 23, 29, 20, 20, NULL, 'Sabbath and Iniquity Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of hypocrisy in observing the Sabbath. Both passages emphasize the consequences for those who prioritize their own needs over righteousness, suggesting a critique of false piety.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 15, 40, 7, 5, 5, 'Thou hypocrite', 'Hypocrisy and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of hypocrisy in both passages. In Luke, the focus is on the hypocrisy of prioritizing animals'' needs over human well-being, while in Matthew, it addresses the hypocrisy of judging others without self-examination.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 16, 41, 2, 27, 27, 'loosed from this bond on the sabbath day', 'Sabbath and Human Need', 'This connection highlights the purpose of the sabbath in relation to human well-being. Both passages emphasize that the sabbath should serve humanity, as seen in the healing of the woman bound for eighteen years.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
